# Scenario: Complex query with filters, pagination, and nesting
# Why: Validates the combination of filtering, pagination (skip/first), and one level of field nesting in a single operation.
query 'CALL graphql::explain("query { transactions(where: { blockNumber_gt: 100 }, skip: 5, first: 10) { hash from { address } } }")'
---
> +-------+----------+----------------------+
> |  idx  |   kind   |        detail        |
> +-------+----------+----------------------+
> |   0   |   From   |     transactions     |
> |   1   |   Join   |     natural from     |
> |   2   |  Filter  |  blockNumber > 100   |
> |   3   |   Skip   |          5           |
> |   4   |   Take   |          10          |
> |   5   |   Map    |  hash, from_address  |
> +-------+----------+----------------------+
>
